  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Drugs with anticholinergic properties are commonly prescribed to older persons despite&#xD;
      growing evidence of their significant adverse effects. However, limited data are available&#xD;
      concerning their contribution to time of onset of delirium. This study aimed to determine the&#xD;
      potential association of higher anticholinergic burden to early-onset of delirium&#xD;
      superimposed dementia in the older adult.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
